results.definition: cause annoyance in; disturb, especially by minor irritations
examples: Mosquitoes buzzing in my ear really bothers me
It irritates me that she never closes the door after she leaves

results.definition: disturb the peace of mind of; afflict with mental agitation or distress
examples: I cannot sleep--my daughter's health is worrying me

results.definition: change the arrangement or position of
subject to prolonged examination, discussion, or deliberation
examples: vex the subject of the death penalty

results.definition: be a mystery or bewildering to
examples: Got me--I don't know the answer!

results.definition: troubled persistently especially with petty annoyances
examples: her poor pestered father had to endure her constant interruptions
the vexed parents of an unruly teenager

results.definition: causing difficulty in finding an answer or solution; much disputed
examples: we live in vexed and troubled times
